CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 28, 1949, pg. 6 reads: "Methodist Women - Women from the several districts which comprise the Washington Annual Conference which met at Warren last week. Snapped in picture, from left to right: Mmes. J. Carter, South Baltimore District; D. M .Pleasants, Virginia Washington District; G. E. Davis of South Baltimore; R. H. Johnson of Washington District; A.P. Shaw, wife of the Bishop; F.  F. King of the North Baltimore; F. D. Tyler, Washington District, M. F. Hayling, of the Charleston District. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Mrs. J. Carter, Mrs. D. M. Pleasants, Mrs. G. E. Davis, Mrs. R. H. Johnson, Mrs. A. P. Shaw, Mrs. F. F. King, Mrs. F. D. Tyler, and Mrs. M. F. Hayling, posed in front of pipe organ in Warren Methodist Church for Washington Annual Conference
